! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|v0.2.2 |2026-05-13 |grouped-tree integration + engine-agnostic node-creation policy + persistent collapse. (0) ''gt:leaf-count forwarding'' — `_applyTooltips` now also surfaces `gt:leaf-count` on each `<me-tpc>` as `data-mm-leaf-count`. New CSS renders a muted ` (N)` badge via `::after`, suppressed by `:has(> me-epd.minus)` so the badge appears only while the node is collapsed (mind-elixir applies `me-epd.minus` to EXPANDED nodes — the negation gives us "show count when collapsed"). (1) New `setAllowNodeCreation(bool)` hook — when `false`, the adapter (a) swallows Tab/Enter at the document-level keydown capture-phase BEFORE mind-elixir's listener runs, and (b) vetos mind-elixir's `addChild`/`insertSibling`/`insertParent`/`finishEdit`-of-placeholder operations from the context menu, restoring the canvas from cached MDOM so any pre-emitted placeholder disappears. Used by views over synthetic-structure producers (e.g. grouped-tree) where there's no tiddler-of-origin for a new node. (2) New top-level `bus.addListener("expandNode", nodeObj)` translates to overlay-store `setAttr core:collapsed` ops (`true` for collapsed, `null` for expanded) so collapse experiments persist instead of vanishing on the next refresh. ''Gotcha:'' mind-elixir fires `expandNode` as its own bus event, NOT under the "operation" channel — adapters must listen separately. (3) New internal `_suspendOpsDuringRefresh` flag toggled around `me.init()` and `me.refresh()` so the synthetic events mind-elixir replays during DOM rebuild don't loop back into the overlay store. Distinct from widget-controlled `setSuspendOps` |
|v0.2.1 |2026-05-13 |Decoration attrs forwarded to DOM. The existing `_applyTooltips` pass now also surfaces `mm:has-slides` on each topic element as `data-mm-has-slides="yes"` (and clears stale attrs when a node no longer has slides). New CSS rule scoped to `.rr-mindmap-slides-only-active me-tpc[data-mm-has-slides="yes"]` paints a `<<colour primary>>` 2px outline so the slides-only view distinguishes nodes that own slides directly from ancestor-only-bearing nodes. Engine-agnostic data-attr convention: wikis can add their own CSS rules without touching the adapter |
|v0.2.0 |2026-05-12 |Wires the structural-editing UX of `rimir/mindmap` v0.2: separate `nodeObj.icons` array so icon emoji don't leak into the editable topic; `setStructural`/`setSuspendOps` hooks; id-existence guard with new-node allowlist; finishEdit-of-placeholder → synthetic `addNode` op; F2 → `requestEditNode`; native delete-confirm; tooltips on nodes; suppression flag around `me.refresh()`+focus restore so cascade refreshes don't wipe the selection-driven preview pane |
|v0.1.0 |2026-05-11 |Initial release. Bundles mind-elixir-core v5.11.0. Implements `mindmapengine` adapter with `capabilities.applyOps=false` (always full update). MDOM ↔ mind-elixir node-data mapping, deep-clone on input, global listener release in destroy() |
